.TH smi-venv-command "1" "October 2025" "SMI Toolset 0.100.0" "SMI Python Command"
.SH NAME
smi-venv-command \- Execute any command inside the local virtual environment
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B smi-venv-command
.I COMMAND
.RI [ ARGUMENTS... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.B smi-venv-command
allows executing any arbitrary \fICOMMAND\fR within the activated local \fB./.venv\fR virtual environment.
If the \fB./.venv\fR directory does not exist, it is automatically created using \fBsmi-create-venv\fR(1) before execution.
.SH AUTHOR
.PP
Command written by Imre Tabur.
Documentation written by Imre Tabur.
